[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Burton is a 59-year-old male with rectal cancer.  Colonoscopy on October 1, 2009 showed obstructing rectal carcinoma.  The biopsy showed moderately differentiated invasive adenocarcinoma.  Rectal EUS on October 2, 2009 demonstrated a 4-cm circumferential rectosigmoid tumor, which appeared to be a T2 lesion in the presence of a peritumoral lymph node.  CT abdomen and pelvis on October 5, 2009 showed rectal carcinoma with pelvic peritoneal metastasis.  He completed preoperative chemoradiation on November 25, 2009.  He comes to the North Branch Medical Clinic for the surgical management on January 4, 2010.

[end section id="20103"]

